    <h1>Covid-19 caused a sharp de&#xAD;cline in milk do&#xAD;na&#xAD;tions in some coun&#xAD;tries</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201207/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-07"><time>2020-12-07</time></a>
        - <span>SCIENCE</span>
        - <span role="byline">PHOTOS: KEVIN LIM, TI&#xAD;MOTHY DAVID, VIVI&#xAD;ENNE LOW STRAITS TIMES GRAPH&#xAD;ICS</span>
    </section>

    <p>• How­ever, the KK Hu­man Milk Bank was able to main­tain a re­serve sup­ply of 60 days of pas­teurised donor hu­man milk (PDHM).</p>
    <p>• KKH stopped ac­cept­ing new donors to re­duce the num­ber of trips moth­ers had to make to hos­pi­tal. There were 31 donors from April to July this year, com­pared with 46 donors in the same pe­riod last year.</p>
    <p>• How­ever, the quan­tity of milk do­nated per donor in­creased, likely be­cause moth­ers were work­ing from home and it was more con­ve­nient for them to pump milk. From April to July, 30 litres of milk were do­nated per donor com­pared with the av­er­age of 12 litres.</p>
    <p>How much milk have donors con­trib­uted?</p>
    <p>53</p>
    <p>The num­ber of women do­nat­ing more than 40 litres 11</p>
    <p>The num­ber of women do­nat­ing more than 100 litres 10</p>
    <p>The num­ber of women do­nat­ing more than 40 litres dur­ing cir­cuit breaker 3</p>
    <p>The num­ber of women do­nat­ing more than 100 litres dur­ing cir­cuit breaker</p>
    <p>•</p>
    <p>•</p>
    <p>Moth­ers who are keen to do­nate can head to www.kkh.com.sg/milk­bank or con­tact 6394-1986</p>


